'''Battlegrounds Mobile India International Cup''' (abbreviated as '''BMIC''') is a [[Battlegrounds Mobile India]] international tournament series.

The 2025 edition is the series' first edition organized by [[KRAFTON]] and features a total prize pool of ₹1,00,00,000 {{Abbr/INR}} with the participation of teams from {{FlagNoLink|in}} India, {{FlagNoLink|kr}} South Korea and {{FlagNoLink|jp}} Japan, fighting for spots into the {{LeagueIconSmall/pubg mobile global championship|date=2025-11-01|}} [[PUBG_Mobile_Global_Championship/2025|2025 PMGC]].

==About==
===Format===
* '''2025 BMIC:''''' October 31st - November 2nd, 2025
** 16 teams:
*** {{Bgcolortext|stayup|8 teams}} from {{FlagNoLink|in}} [[Battlegrounds_Mobile_India_Showdown/2025|2025 BMSD]]
*** {{Bgcolortext|stayup|4 teams}} from {{FlagNoLink|kr}} [[PUBG_Mobile_Pro_Series/2025/Season_2|2025 PMPS S2]]
*** {{Bgcolortext|stayup|4 teams}} from {{FlagNoLink|jp}} [[PUBG_Mobile_Japan_League/Season_5/Phase_2|2025 PMJL P2]]
** 18 matches (6 each day).
